parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loss of Power and Acceleration After Stalling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and acceleration after stalling can lead to dangerous situations, especially on highways, making it difficult to merge or maintain speed, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls and upon restarting
it accelerates extremely slowly
unable to reach normal speeds
often limited to 20-40 mph
even with the gas pedal fully depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power or unexplained limp mode can lead to accidents, as the vehicle may be unable to accelerate or maintain speed, putting the driver and others at risk.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
takes a long time to accelerate
and may not respond to pressing the gas pedal. The issue may occur intermittently
and the vehicle may not display any warning lights or error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation under the hood can lead to electrical system failures, corrosion, and other issues that can affect vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: Water collects under the hood
potentially causing electrical system failures or other issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning driver side visor can obstruct the driver's view, making it difficult to drive safely, especially in city streets.
symptoms: The driver side visor falls straight down
blocking the driver's view
and may not hold its position.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Power Loss after Restart
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and subsequent power loss can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, making it difficult to keep up with traffic, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalls
power loss after restarting
difficulty maintaining speed
especially when climbing hills
and reduced acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of acceleration can lead to life-threatening situations, especially when driving on highways, as it can cause the vehicle to slow down unexpectedly, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The vehicle loses acceleration
unable to exceed 30mph in any gear
even with the accelerator pedal pushed to the floor
sudden drop in speed without warning
failure to accelerate after restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the VDC (Vehicle Dynamic Control) system can cause unpredictable power loss, making it difficult to accelerate or maintain speed, which can lead to accidents or put the driver and others at risk.
symptoms: Upon restarting the vehicle after stalling
the VDC system limits engine power
applies the brakes
and causes the car to perform unpredictably
making it difficult to accelerate or maintain speed.
